    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="819"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/946</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dorsey</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="45" xml:id="d819fn45">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Minister in his despatch No. 1965, March 12; received April 15,
                        1929.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-12">March 12,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg leave to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    despatch No. 275, of February 15, 1929,<note n="46" xml:id="d819fn46">Not
                        printed.</note> and No. 276, of February 21, 1929, in <pb facs="0949"
                        n="805" xml:id="pg_805"/> regard to existing discrimination against American
                    interests in the collection of customs surtaxes at Tsingtao.</p>
                <p>You should make a formal protest to the local authorities against the non-payment
                    by the Japanese of this surtax, which constitutes a discrimination against
                    American interests, and at the same time you are authorized to use your good
                    offices with the Customs Surtax Bureau to the end that all merchandise
                    contracted for by American interests for export prior to the date of the
                    promulgation of the surtaxes should be exempted from its operation.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. V. A. MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
